29:47.786 --> 29:50.580
that you can fix this on your own,
'cause you can't. We can.

29:52.999 --> 29:57.378
(SIGHS) I got some cats hassling me,
who I hope Troy ain't mixed up with.

29:57.504 --> 29:59.714
and I don't want them following me
back to my apartment.

30:00.089 --> 30:02.634
So don't even bother asking me
to give you any info on 'em

30:02.884 --> 30:05.094
-'cause I won't do it.
-Where's your place?

30:06.054 --> 30:09.933
Williamsburg, by the bridge,
1820 South 9th Street.

30:10.475 --> 30:13.686
-If this comes back to you, slick...
-I didn't do a damn thing.

30:15.146 --> 30:17.398
You know, except... lie to y'all earlier.

30:17.732 --> 30:18.775
Sit tight.

30:30.829 --> 30:31.913
Take the back.

30:38.753 --> 30:40.505
-MALE VOICE: What?
-Police! Open the door!

30:43.508 --> 30:44.676
-Back up.
-All right, relax!

30:45.051 --> 30:46.761
I said back up,
or I'll blow his brains out!

30:46.970 --> 30:48.680
-TROY: Don't let him kill me, man!
-MALE VOICE: Put your guns down!

30:48.847 --> 30:50.765
-That ain't happening.
-Put it down, or I'm gonna shoot his ass!

30:50.974 --> 30:52.559
We can work this out,
but we're not putting our guns down.

30:52.642 --> 30:54.394
MALE VOICE: I'm getting in this car,
and we're getting out of here!

30:54.477 --> 30:55.812
-Get in the car. Relax.
-You stay right there,

30:55.895 --> 30:58.147
or I'm gonna shoot his ass! Go! Go! Go!

30:58.273 --> 31:00.149
-MALE VOICE: Go!
-All right, come on.

31:00.608 --> 31:02.652
-(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)
-(TIRES SCREECHING)

31:05.029 --> 31:07.740
-(SIRENS WAILING)
-(TIRES SCREECHING)

31:07.866 --> 31:09.284
JOHN JR.: We got 15th Squad to Central K.

31:09.576 --> 31:13.538
This unit in pursuit of a silver sedan
in the 9-4 Precinct.

31:14.038 --> 31:15.874
-(TIRES SCREECHING)
-(CARS HONKING)

31:18.710 --> 31:20.879
We got a suspect with a kidnap victim,

31:20.962 --> 31:24.257
-guns involved, turning north on...
-What a stupid son of a bitch...

31:26.426 --> 31:27.760
Watch out!

31:27.969 --> 31:30.263
-(TIRES SCREECHING)
-(SIRENS WAILING)

31:34.684 --> 31:36.769
Unit's heading west on 5th Street.

31:43.943 --> 31:46.237
-Watch it!
-Turning north on 10th!

31:46.946 --> 31:48.740
(CARS HONKING)

31:49.032 --> 31:50.575
(TIRES SCREECHING)

31:50.742 --> 31:52.911
-Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!
-MALE VOICE: Hey, watch it, jerk!

31:53.870 --> 31:56.748
-(TIRES SCREECHING)
-(SIRENS WAILING)

32:03.379 --> 32:04.797
ANDY: Look at this dumb asshole.

32:05.423 --> 32:06.883
Whoa, whoa!

32:09.510 --> 32:10.720
Oh, man!

32:12.639 --> 32:15.058
(SIRENS WAILING)

32:16.184 --> 32:17.602
-ANDY: Let's see your hands!
-Get out! Let's go!

32:17.810 --> 32:19.938
Let's go. Let's go.
Get out. Get out.

32:20.104 --> 32:21.606
This guy needs an ambulance!

32:21.814 --> 32:23.149
-You got him?
-Yeah, I got him.

32:23.316 --> 32:24.525
ANDY: You just take it easy, Troy.

32:24.692 --> 32:26.861
-I thought I was gonna die!
-Yeah, well, you're lucky you didn't.

32:26.945 --> 32:29.822
-I didn't know what to do. My family...
-All right. Shut up and sit still.

32:41.709 --> 32:44.379
-I'd really like to talk to my wife.
-Well, you need to talk to us first, Troy.

32:44.587 --> 32:45.922
I just want to let her know I'm all right.

32:46.047 --> 32:47.131
She knows.

32:47.256 --> 32:49.008
All right. What the hell was that
about back on the street?

32:49.509 --> 32:51.511
If I'm honest,
does that count for anything?

32:51.678 --> 32:54.347
-ANDY: Absolutely.
-I lost my job.

32:55.723 --> 32:59.018
Me and my wife, we got two young girls.
I'm looking at losing everything.

32:59.894 --> 33:00.979
I know it was wrong...

33:01.062 --> 33:02.855
All right, Troy,
we need to hear about today.

33:03.022 --> 33:04.899
JOHN JR.: And we know
how you met Bob Drazin

33:04.983 --> 33:07.026
at a homeless shelter
and he tipped you off

33:07.110 --> 33:10.321
to his boss having a lot of money
at the apartment, but how did it go down?

33:12.657 --> 33:15.326
Those two guys back there,
T.K. and Robbie,

33:15.702 --> 33:16.828
I was in it with them.

33:17.203 --> 33:19.747
But the old man,
once we got in the apartment,

33:19.998 --> 33:21.374
he wouldn't give up the money.

33:21.666 --> 33:24.085
So, T.K And Robbie,
they started to lay into him.

33:24.502 --> 33:28.381
I wasn't down for that.
I told 'em to chill, they don't listen,

33:29.507 --> 33:32.135
so I go in the back to book,
Robbie catches me,

33:32.552 --> 33:34.303
pulls out his gun,
like he's gonna take me out.

33:34.554 --> 33:37.807
He turned his back. That's when I hit
the fire escape, and I was gone.

33:37.932 --> 33:39.767
So they followed you
to your cousin's apartment?

33:40.018 --> 33:41.019
They must have.

33:41.185 --> 33:43.229
All I know is they got there
just before you guys did.

33:44.856 --> 33:47.608
-The old man, he live?
-Yeah.

33:47.859 --> 33:50.611
All right, getting hooked up
with T.K. And Robbie,

33:50.987 --> 33:54.532
-did you go through your cousin for that?
-No. We talked about it.

33:54.782 --> 33:57.243
We was just gonna give
the whole deal to Corey and take a cut,

33:57.326 --> 33:59.579
like Drazin was doing,
but I left Corey out of it

33:59.704 --> 34:01.456
and went straight to T.K.
and Robbie on my own,

34:01.539 --> 34:02.957
and that was a big mistake.

34:03.249 --> 34:06.252
When "we" talked about it, who's "we"?

34:07.128 --> 34:08.296
You and your wife?

34:09.255 --> 34:12.300
She never did nothing!
All we did was talk about it.

34:16.012 --> 34:17.889
Can I please just talk to her?

34:24.896 --> 34:27.482
This is a simple story of vengeance.

34:27.690 --> 34:30.902
The defendant's personal
and professional lives had come apart.

34:31.235 --> 34:35.114
He told everyone in earshot
Lieutenant Rodriguez was to blame.

34:35.281 --> 34:37.575
Then he sought out his victim,
and he shot him

34:37.658 --> 34:39.702
in an alcohol-induced rage.

34:40.328 --> 34:44.707
You don't need anything more to convict,
ladies and gentlemen, but you have more.

34:45.166 --> 34:48.377
Eighteen months
of frivolous investigations

34:48.503 --> 34:50.463
that failed to yield results.

34:51.130 --> 34:53.925
And years of smoldering resentment.

34:54.550 --> 34:57.970
And the damning testimonies
of six witnesses,

34:58.054 --> 35:00.640
including the defendant's
own co-workers.

35:00.890 --> 35:03.351
What testimony does the defendant offer?

35:03.643 --> 35:06.938
A career criminal
the lieutenant had put away twice,

35:07.396 --> 35:09.774
a cop who contradicted that criminal

35:09.857 --> 35:13.152
and the defendant's own
self-serving statements.

35:14.529 --> 35:18.116
But the defendant asks you
to believe the unbelievable.

35:18.282 --> 35:23.371
That the lieutenant would risk everything
to kill a discredited man.

35:23.538 --> 35:27.458
Whose bogus investigations were,
at worst, a nuisance.

35:28.376 --> 35:35.133
That a drunk drew his pistol and fired
before a sober man unholstered his weapon.

35:36.008 --> 35:40.555
On that day, Captain Fraker,
a drunk, disgraced adulterer,

35:40.638 --> 35:45.143
walked into Lieutenant Rodriguez' office,
and unprovoked, shot him.

35:45.518 --> 35:49.355
I ask you to find Captain Fraker guilty.

35:50.314 --> 35:51.607
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen.

36:00.616 --> 36:04.620
Let's look at the prosecution's
vaunted witnesses,

36:05.121 --> 36:08.291
detectives in Tony Rodriguez's
own command,

36:08.457 --> 36:12.545
a doctor who was sleeping
with one of those detectives,

36:12.837 --> 36:15.214
an underling bucking for a promotion,

36:15.965 --> 36:17.758
an angry ex-girlfriend.

36:18.843 --> 36:23.264
The prosecution has not offered you
a single unbiased witness,

36:23.764 --> 36:26.809
not one. So forget the witnesses.

36:27.393 --> 36:30.605
Because only two men know
what really happened in that office.

36:30.730 --> 36:33.274
Captain Fraker had been coming
for Tony Rodriguez.

36:34.066 --> 36:36.652
Five investigations in 18 months.

36:37.111 --> 36:40.323
The latest concerning serious charges
that have never been refuted.

36:40.740 --> 36:44.535
You don't think Tony Rodriguez
wanted to be rid of the captain?

36:45.119 --> 36:46.412
You bet he did.

36:46.829 --> 36:49.498
And whether these two men
disliked each other

36:49.582 --> 36:53.544
and for whatever reason is irrelevant
to the only facts that matter.

36:54.212 --> 36:57.632
It all comes down
to who you want to believe.

36:58.883 --> 37:03.721
A cop, who's been the target
of investigations involving corruption

37:04.055 --> 37:05.348
and excessive force,

37:05.932 --> 37:11.854
or a cop who has spent his entire career
protecting our city, fighting corruption,

37:12.521 --> 37:15.900
and rooting out cops
who use excessive force.

37:16.359 --> 37:18.945
Remember your job,
ladies and gentlemen of the jury.

37:19.195 --> 37:23.324
If you have any reasonable doubt
about the prosecution's case,

37:23.824 --> 37:28.037
you must find Captain Fraker not guilty.

37:39.715 --> 37:41.342
-You get Troy to central booking?
-ANDY: Yeah.

37:41.801 --> 37:43.094
How about the other two clowns?

37:43.177 --> 37:45.012
-They're being treated at Bellevue.
-TONY: Any word on that?

37:45.221 --> 37:47.556
One's got a busted pelvis,
the other guy's under the knife

37:47.682 --> 37:49.016
for internal bleeding. He's up in the air.

37:49.350 --> 37:52.311
Uniforms are sitting on both of them.
I notified the borough to keep tabs.

37:53.145 --> 37:54.772
All right. Good night.

37:56.315 --> 37:57.316
Uh, boss...

37:58.276 --> 38:00.861
down at Mac's, they have this thing,
I don't know if you've heard of it before

38:00.987 --> 38:03.030
it's called "cold beer."
And let me tell you,

38:03.489 --> 38:06.033
they invented it in response
to that look on your face.

38:06.409 --> 38:07.451
Maybe...

38:07.702 --> 38:09.996
JOHN JR.: Apparently, money.
Which I currently have in my pocket,

38:10.579 --> 38:11.789
can purchase this item.

38:12.248 --> 38:13.582
Well, I guess you're buying.

38:15.334 --> 38:18.546
-Field trip, down to Mac's, anybody?
-I'm in.

38:18.713 --> 38:19.797
I'm in, sure.

38:21.716 --> 38:23.134
See if you can get Valerie
to join us, huh?

38:23.968 --> 38:25.428
I'll meet you over there.

38:26.387 --> 38:28.055
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

38:30.516 --> 38:33.019
-Go ahead, John. I got it.
-I'll see you there.

38:35.938 --> 38:37.773
-Where's Troy?
-Jail.

38:38.065 --> 38:39.859
Oh, my God. Um, for what?

38:40.151 --> 38:41.944
He didn't hand that job over to Corey.

38:42.194 --> 38:44.864
-Like the two of you talked about.
-Talked about?

38:45.156 --> 38:47.742
Because you played games this morning
to keep your name out of it,

38:47.867 --> 38:50.453
-your husband almost got killed.
-I told you about Corey.

38:50.703 --> 38:52.872
And you left out the other 99 percent.

38:54.665 --> 38:55.875
We're completely broke.

38:56.250 --> 38:58.169
Troy was just supposed
to tell Corey about it...

38:58.419 --> 39:00.796
The only reason I'm not locking you up
is 'cause you got kids at home,

39:00.880 --> 39:03.382
and they don't deserve
to be in some institution.

39:08.888 --> 39:11.182
-ANDREA: How long is Troy going away for?
-Ask your lawyer.

39:11.891 --> 39:13.851
Can you please just tell me?

39:15.102 --> 39:17.605
He's looking at a couple of years,
at least.

39:18.022 --> 39:19.190
Oh, my God.

39:20.274 --> 39:21.400
All right, we're done.

39:22.109 --> 39:23.444
Go home now to your kids.

39:35.164 --> 39:38.584
And so, we're in the squad,
doing a late tour,

39:38.834 --> 39:40.628
and McCuskey comes back from dinner

39:40.753 --> 39:43.297
-with this huge hickey on his neck.
-Oh, boy.

39:43.631 --> 39:47.051
I knew McCuskey in Queens homicide.
Big time skirt chaser.

39:47.426 --> 39:51.347
So, he's got two hours left
before he has to head home to his wife.

39:51.764 --> 39:53.849
And he's begging us
to help him get rid of it.

39:53.933 --> 39:55.101
Oh, yeah. They don't come off.

39:55.184 --> 39:58.104
GREG: So, McCuskey goes
to the utility closet,

39:58.270 --> 40:00.481
and he comes out with a wire brush.

40:00.689 --> 40:03.943
He takes two pulls of whiskey
from his hip flask,

40:04.777 --> 40:08.239
and he rakes his neck bloody
to cover the hickey.

40:08.531 --> 40:09.532
-Oh.
-GREG: He goes home,

40:09.949 --> 40:13.911
he tells his wife a perp did it,
and she actually buys it!

40:13.994 --> 40:15.704
(LAUGHS)

40:19.792 --> 40:21.460
Yeah, I think I'm gonna get going.

40:21.710 --> 40:23.087
-Yeah?
-Yeah, I'm beat.

40:23.421 --> 40:24.505
Thanks for the beer.

40:26.674 --> 40:29.385
I think I'm out, too. I'll be in touch.

40:29.635 --> 40:31.345
All right, I'll settle up
and walk you to your car.

40:33.931 --> 40:36.934
-Hey, wanna lose at darts?
-Um, I think I'm heading out, too.

40:37.935 --> 40:38.936
Good night.

40:39.520 --> 40:41.313
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

40:41.939 --> 40:43.899
(SIGHS) Probably should have
kept my mouth shut.

40:44.233 --> 40:46.819
It was fine, Greg.
It... it lightened things up.

40:47.194 --> 40:50.990
I'm sure Andy has a differing opinion.
In fact, I'm certain of it.

40:51.866 --> 40:55.119
Look, if I been on you too hard,
I don't mean nothing by it.

40:55.369 --> 40:57.496
Just looking forward for this being over.

40:59.665 --> 41:00.708
Yeah.

41:07.882 --> 41:10.050
-RITA: Hey.
-What's up?

41:10.509 --> 41:13.012
Nothing. Um, can I catch a ride home?

41:13.429 --> 41:15.806
I was gonna drive down to the seaport,
take a walk.

41:16.056 --> 41:17.099
I got time.

41:18.392 --> 41:19.518
Sure, okay.

41:28.152 --> 41:30.946
My first real collar
was this guy Ralph Maldonado.

41:31.780 --> 41:34.450
I finally got him
on receiving stolen goods,

41:34.533 --> 41:39.038
but he was notorious for shaking down
local businesses for protection money.

41:39.997 --> 41:43.584
So satisfying because Ralph
was the exact type of guy

41:43.667 --> 41:46.045
that made me wanna get on the job
in the first place.

41:46.670 --> 41:47.713
A bully.

41:48.464 --> 41:50.174
That's why I wanted to become a cop.

41:51.509 --> 41:52.885
You're getting way ahead of yourself.

41:53.427 --> 41:54.803
What do you mean?
I'm just telling you a story.

41:55.095 --> 41:57.264
-You're giving your own eulogy.
-You got it wrong.

41:57.681 --> 41:58.891
No, that's what you're doing.

41:59.016 --> 42:01.560
And you're way off,
because the jury's gonna convict Fraker,

42:01.644 --> 42:03.229
and everything is gonna be everything.

42:10.110 --> 42:14.323
I guess, I'm just saying that I'm proud
of the time I put on the job.

42:14.532 --> 42:16.367
Well, you got a lot more years
ahead of you.

42:16.534 --> 42:17.952
A lot more good you can do.

42:21.247 --> 42:22.289
I hope so.

42:31.966 --> 42:36.011
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

42:59.577 --> 43:01.704
(MUSIC CONCLUDES)
